The subject consists of three parts: Golour Studies, Study of Composition and Study of Perspective. Itten`s,  Edward`s  and Lapin's work have been used to apply theoretical knowledge into practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main aim is to introduce the most important parts of structure of Art Studies and creative work; as well as form theoretical, practical and methodological skills for teaching in elementary school.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course:
- knows the structure of Art and Art Studies;
- understands the basic rules of colour studies, compositions and perspective;
- knows the terminology related to the domains of colour studies, compositions and perspective and is able to analyze  a piece of work and students`work accordingly;
- applies his/her theoretical, didactis and practical skills in creative work.
